# Acknowledgements

## Overview

The Divan and the Sword (TDS) recognizes the contributions of the broader scholarly community whose research, critical editions, archival resources, and digital infrastructures make historical research possible.

This project builds upon centuries of scholarship while striving to contribute transparently and responsibly to future research.

---

## Scholarly Tradition

TDS acknowledges the work of historians, philologists, political theorists, literary scholars, archivists, librarians, and digital humanists whose efforts preserve and expand knowledge of the Iranian and Persianate world.

---

## Libraries and Archives

Historical research depends upon libraries, archives, museums, manuscript collections, and digital repositories that preserve documentary heritage for future generations.

---

## Open Scholarship

The project supports the principles of open scholarship, transparent documentation, reproducible research, and responsible academic communication.

---

## Digital Infrastructure

Modern historical research benefits from sustainable digital infrastructure, open-source software, persistent identifiers, and institutional repositories that improve long-term accessibility.

---

## Future Collaborations

As the project develops, collaborations, institutional partnerships, and scholarly contributions may be acknowledged here where appropriate.

